<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Template Manager</title>
    <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
	<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
	<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/icon?family=Material+Icons" rel="stylesheet">
    <%= stylesheet_link_tag    'application', media: 'all', 'data-turbolinks-track': 'reload' %>
    <%= javascript_include_tag 'application', 'data-turbolinks-track': 'reload' %>
  </head>

  <body style="background-color: ">
  <header>
  </header>
  <main style="padding-left: 0;">
  <div class="container" style="padding-top: 5%;">
      <div class="row">
      	<div class="col m2"></div>
        <div class="col s12 m8">
          <div class="card blue-grey darken-1 horizontal">
          	
          	<div class="card-image">
        		<!--<img src="https://lorempixel.com/100/190/nature/6">
        		<i class="material-icons dp48">settings</i>-->
      		</div>
            
            <div class="card-stacked">
            	<div class="card-content white-text">
            		<span class="card-title">We're all set!</span>
              <p>Awesome! Setup wizard is now finished and Template Manager is configured.</p><br>
              <p><a href="/machines" style="color: white; text-decoration: underline;">You can reach the dashboard from here</a></p><br>

            	<p>A slight overview from wizard:</p>
              <ul>
              	<%= apistatuscheck %>
                <%= rdpcredentialscheck %>
          		  <%= masteraccountcheck %>
              </ul>
                <p>If all indicators show <span style="color: #1de9b6">green</span>, lock down the setup wizard by clicking <%= link_to "here", { :action => "lock"}, method: "PATCH", remote: "true", style: "color: white; text-decoration: underline;" %> before going to dashboard.</p>
            	</div>
        	<div class="card-action">
          		<a href="/machines">Go to Dashboard</a>
        	</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col m2"></div>
      </div>
</div>
  </main>
  </body>
</html>